summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeDiscover Morphe eyeshadows, remastered, with the ChromaPlus 12-Pan Eyeshadow Palette. Powered by a ChromaPlus blend, these shadow formulas deliver pigment-packed performance and all-day wear. Effortlessly build dimension with luxuriously blendable mattes, shimmers, and metallics.
details: DetailsFeatures12 eyeshadows in cool-toned neutrals & graysDimension-building mattes, shimmers & metallicsPersonal application mirror for on-the-go artistryShadesTop Row: Speed of Light (matte buff), Just a Phase (matte bisque), Extra Alienating (matte soft taupe), Rocket to Riches (matte cool brown)Middle Row: Otherearthly (matte slate), Galactic Gem (shimmering gray), Lucky Stars (metallic icy white), Opulent Orbit (metallic ashy taupe)Bottom Row: Space Age (metallic silver), Nocturnal Nova (metallic graphite), Cocoa Cosmos (matte warm brown), Total Eclipse (matte charcoal)Research ResultsThe majority of consumers agreed ChromaPlus eyeshadows deliver:Highly pigmented, single-swipe color payoff*Non-patchy, seamless, even application*Silky-smooth, buttery-soft texture*Effortless application**Based on a 21-person consumer perception study.Item 2641278How To UseFor a seamlessly diffused effect, apply matte shades with a fluffy blending brush. For more precise application, such as to line and define your lash lines, apply matte shades with a smaller detail brush.Pack shimmer and metallic shades onto your lids by pressing them on with your fingertip for intense payoff or by using a flat packer brush.Layer different shade finishes to create depth; blend mattes to build your base, press shimmers onto the centers of your lids or inner eye corners for brightness, and top with metallics for a high-impact finish.IngredientsSpeed Of Light, Just A Phase, Extra Alienating, Rocket To Riches, Otherearthly: Talc, Mica, Silica, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Magnesium Stearate, Dimethicone, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Octyldodecyl Stearoyl Stearate, Boron Nitride, Phenoxyethanol, Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Tocopheryl Acetate, Lauroyl Lysine, Magnesium Myristate, Hydroxyapatite, Kaolin, Mangifera Indica (Mango) Seed Oil, Caprylyl Glycol, Ethylhexylglycerin, Zinc Oxide, Tocopherol. reviews.headline: Big NO
reviews.comments: I was expecting SO MUCH MORE from this brand- especially after having hundreds of lawsuits against them for using non eye safe ingredients in eyeshadow. these are still not eye safe at ALL. the glitters are large, chunky, scratchy. I now have a scratched and damaged eye and I'm a care provider for a blind person and I cant even do that right now. returned so fast- I'm sickened.

reviews.headline: Underrated beginner palette
reviews.comments: I bought this palette for one of my best friends 30th birthday. She is not a makeup girly at all, so I decided that I would get her started with a good, quality, neutral palette. She's been absolutely loving it. The shadows blend seamlessly and the pigment is high quality. As someone who's owned Pat McGrath, HUDA, Urban Decay, ABH, and more, I was shockingly surprised by the quality and payoff these shadows have. Again, great neutral palette and beginner friendly.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Morphe's Rose Frequency Eyeshadow Palette has exceeded all of my expectations! The new 12-pan palette has gorgeous metallics, shimmers, and mattes that all compliment each other. They are silky smooth and make building dimension with your eyeshadow a breeze because they are completely blendable. You can choose any color on the palette and it will compliment all of the other color choices, effortlessly! I love the vibrant hues and the pigments of this palette. It glides on smoothly and feels so silky. On top of all that, they have staying-power. I mixed different shades, such as the shade in pan 1 with pan 6 and 12, beautiful dimension with no creases. You can choose any metallic shade to layer onto a shimmer shade, then add even more dimension with a finishing matte shade, seamlessly. They last all day with no need for touchups. I live in a very humid climate so I know how hard creasing can be to overcome with any kind of eyeshadow, but Morphe has really set the gold standard in eyeshadow with this palette. 
         The case is also beautiful with a mirror that is great for on-the-go application. It has gorgeous detail and you can really feel the quality in how it's made. I have tried an assortment of combinations with this palette and you cannot go wrong--the colors all compliment each other! The shimmers have classic shade tones that are super-easy to build upon so there are endless options here. From classic to modern trends, it really has it all. You can combine these shades to transform your look from classic metallic shine combinations to bold/vibrant/standout-shimmers, you cannot go wrong with this palette. I am obsessed with it and it feels smooth and silky with no creasing. The shades all compliment the other shades so you can combine any 2, 3, 4 or more to build depth and dimension to your look. The vibrant hues are amazing and make it super-easy, even for beginners in the cosmetic world.
faceoff_positive.headline: Beautiful complimentary colors that don't crease!

faceoff_negative.comments: I received this eyeshadow palette from Buzzagent and Morphe for free in exchange for my honest review.  The colors in the rose palette are very pretty and mostly have a warm undertone. The case has a large mirror on the inside of the lid which is very nice. They are not very pigmented but you are able to build up the color.  There is a lot of fallout from the shades with glitter. Upon initial application, the glitter was all over my cheekbones. I brushed off the fallout but throughout the day I would notice more glitter under my eyes and on my cheeks.  Using my fingertips to apply did not help it stay on my eyelids any better. My eyelids are slightly oily and the eyeshadows ended up creasing when I wore them for longer hours.  The color fades a bit throughout the day but if you use a primer it helps to keep it from fading and the initial application is more pigmented.  Overall, I think there are better eyeshadows that don't have as much fallout, but these colors are nice for the spring.
faceoff_negative.headline: Nice everyday eye palette
